 cell surface. Based on the Orfeome, Frp1 localizes at the cell surface.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nand\\r\\n\\\"Concerning your questions, as far as know, there are no papers reporting any functional roles for Frp1 and Frp2 with respect to siderophore (ferrichrome) uptake in S pombe.\\\"\\r\\n\\r\\nSo it seems PomBase and SGD @edwong57  are using the wrong term here, and I cannot find the correct term.\\r\\nI will transfer this to the ontology tracker for the new term.\\r\\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2024-04-12T13:18:29Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27593#issuecomment-2051750058\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws6fbsB1\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778378656171,"end":1778378656246}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09275248f1c079820169ffe7a011a88196842ed2a5a31a298d"}},"id":"prt_e0fa0c978001sY5AXmRP3epA1H","sessionID":"ses_1f05f45a7ffeh66rel7RWpqDJH","messageID":"msg_e0fa0bb01001mYmAFa7EpVhkUt"}}
