Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\")\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliations\n\n-   1 D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\n-   2 Biological Sciences, Integrative Cell Biology, University of Calgary, Calgary, Alberta, Canada.\n\n-   PMID: **34614242**\n-   DOI: [10.1111/mmi.14829](https://doi.org/10.1111/mmi.14829)\n\nFree article\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\n# Fission yeast RNA-binding proteins Puf2 and Puf4 are involved in repression of ferrireductase Frp1 expression in response to iron\n\nJude Beaudoin¬†et al. Mol Microbiol. 2021 Nov.\n\nFree article\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nMol Microbiol\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Mol+Microbiol%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Mol+Microbiol%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2021 Nov;116(5):1361-1377.\n\ndoi: 10.1111/mmi.14829. Epub 2021 Oct 21.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Jude Beaudoin](/?term=Beaudoin+J&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\") ,¬†[Vincent Normant](/?term=Normant+V&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\") ,¬†[Ariane Brault](/?term=Brault+A&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\") ,¬†[Darren J Henry](/?term=Henry+DJ&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [2](#short-view-affiliation-2 \"Biological Sciences, Integrative Cell Biology, University of Calgary, Calgary, Alberta, Canada.\") ,¬†[Fran√ßois Bachand](/?term=Bachand+F&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\") ,¬†[√Čric Mass√©](/?term=Mass%C3%A9+%C3%89&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\") ,¬†[Gordon Chua](/?term=Chua+G&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [2](#short-view-affiliation-2 \"Biological Sciences, Integrative Cell Biology, University of Calgary, Calgary, Alberta, Canada.\") ,¬†[Simon Labb√©](/?term=Labb%C3%A9+S&cauthor_id=34614242)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\")\n\n### Affiliations\n\n-   1 D√©partement de Biochimie et de G√©nomique Fonctionnelle, Facult√© de m√©decine et des sciences de la sant√©, Universit√© de Sherbrooke, Sherbrooke, Quebec, Canada.\n-   2 Biological Sciences, Integrative Cell Biology, University of Calgary, Calgary, Alberta, Canada.\n\n-   PMID: **34614242**\n-   DOI: [10.1111/mmi.14829](https://doi.org/10.1111/mmi.14829)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nThis study identifies a post-transcriptional mechanism of iron uptake regulation by Puf2 and Puf4 of the Pumilio and FBF (Puf) family of RNA-binding proteins in Schizosaccharomyces pombe. Cells expressing Puf2 and Puf4 stimulate decay of the frp1+ mRNA encoding a key enzyme of the reductive iron uptake pathway. Results consistently showed that frp1+ mRNA is stabilized in puf2őĒ puf4őĒ mutant cells under iron-replete conditions. As a result, puf2őĒ puf4őĒ cells exhibit an increased sensitivity to iron accompanied by enhanced ferrireductase activity. A pool of GFP-frp1+ 3'UTR RNAs was generated using a reporter gene containing the 3' untranslated region (UTR) of frp1+ that was under the control of a regulatable promoter. Results showed that Puf2 and Puf4 accelerate the destabilization of mRNAs containing the frp1+ 3'UTR which harbors two Pumilio response elements (PREs). Binding studies revealed that the PUM-homology RNA-binding domain of Puf2 and Puf4 expressed in Escherichia coli specifically interacts with PREs in the frp1+ 3'UTR. Using RNA immunoprecipitation in combination with reverse transcription qPCR assays, results showed that Puf2 and Puf4 interact preferentially with frp1+ mRNA under basal and iron-replete conditions, thereby contributing to inhibit Frp1 production and protecting cells against toxic levels of iron.\n\n**Keywords:** PUF protein family; RNA-binding protein; fission yeast; iron homeostasis; iron-regulated genes.\n\n¬© 2021 John Wiley & Sons Ltd.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## References\n\n#### REFERENCES\n\n1.  1.  Askwith, C. & Kaplan, J. (1997) An oxidase-permease-based iron transport system in Schizosaccharomyces pombe and its expression in saccharomyces cerevisiae. Journal of Biological Chemistry, 272(1), 401-405. [https://doi.org/10.1074/jbc.272.1.401](https://doi.org/10.1074/jbc.272.1.401)\n2.  1.  Bahler, J., Wu, J.Q., Longtine, M.S., Shah, N.G., McKenzie, A. 3rd, Steever, A.B. et al (1998) Heterologous modules for efficient and versatile PCR-based gene targeting in Schizosaccharomyces pombe. Yeast, 14(10), 943-951. [https://doi.org/10.1002/(SICI)1097-0061(199807)14:10<943:AID-YEA292&g...](https://doi.org/10.1002/\\(SICI\\)1097-0061\\(199807\\)14:10<943:AID-YEA292>3.0.CO;2-Y)\n3.  1.  Beaudoin, J., Lalibert√©, J. & Labb√©, S. (2006) Functional dissection of Ctr4 and Ctr5 amino-terminal regions reveals motifs with redundant roles in copper transport. Microbiology, 152(Pt 1), 209-222. [https://doi.org/10.1099/mic.0.28392-0](https://doi.org/10.1099/mic.0.28392-0)\n4.  1.  Brault, A., Mourer, T. & Labb√©, S. (2015) Molecular basis of the regulation of iron homeostasis in fission and filamentous yeasts. IUBMB Life, 67(11), 801-815. [https://doi.org/10.1002/iub.1441](https://doi.org/10.1002/iub.1441)\n5.  1.  Chen, D., Toone, W.M., Mata, J., Lyne, R., Burns, G., Kivinen, K. et al (2003) Global transcriptional responses of fission yeast to environmental stress. Molecular Biology of the Cell, 14(1), 214-229. [https://doi.org/10.1091/mbc.E02-08-0499](https://doi.org/10.1091/mbc.E02-08-0499)\n\nShow all 63 references\n\n## Publication types\n\n-   Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t%22%5Bpt%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   3' Untranslated Regions\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%223%27+Untranslated+Regions%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=3%27+Untranslated+Regions)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   DNA, Fungal\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22DNA%2C+Fungal%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=DNA%2C+Fungal)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   FMN Reductase / genetics\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22FMN+Reductase%2Fgenetics%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=FMN+Reductase)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   FMN Reductase / metabolism\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   