Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Mol+Cell+Biol%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Mol+Cell+Biol%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 1993 Jul;13(7):4342-50.\n\ndoi: 10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993.\n\n# The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase\n\n[D G Roman](/?term=Roman+DG&cauthor_id=8321236)¬† [1](#full-view-affiliation-1 \"Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\") ,¬†[A Dancis](/?term=Dancis+A&cauthor_id=8321236),¬†[G J Anderson](/?term=Anderson+GJ&cauthor_id=8321236),¬†[R D Klausner](/?term=Klausner+RD&cauthor_id=8321236)\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\n\n-   PMID: **8321236**\n-   PMCID: [PMC359993](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC359993/)\n-   DOI: [10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993](https://doi.org/10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\n# The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase\n\nD G Roman¬†et al. Mol Cell Biol. 1993 Jul.\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nMol Cell Biol\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Mol+Cell+Biol%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Mol+Cell+Biol%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 1993 Jul;13(7):4342-50.\n\ndoi: 10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993.\n\n### Authors\n\n[D G Roman](/?term=Roman+DG&cauthor_id=8321236)¬† [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\") ,¬†[A Dancis](/?term=Dancis+A&cauthor_id=8321236),¬†[G J Anderson](/?term=Anderson+GJ&cauthor_id=8321236),¬†[R D Klausner](/?term=Klausner+RD&cauthor_id=8321236)\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\n\n-   PMID: **8321236**\n-   PMCID: [PMC359993](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC359993/)\n-   DOI: [10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993](https://doi.org/10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nWe have identified a cell surface ferric reductase activity in the fission yeast Schizosaccharomyces pombe. A mutant strain deficient in this activity was also deficient in ferric iron uptake, while ferrous iron uptake was not impaired. Therefore, reduction is a required step in cellular ferric iron acquisition. We have cloned frp1+, the wild-type allele of the mutant gene. frp1+ mRNA levels were repressed by iron addition to the growth medium. Fusion of 138 nucleotides of frp1+ promoter sequences to a reporter gene, the bacterial chloramphenicol acetyltransferase gene, conferred iron-dependent regulation upon the latter when introduced into S. pombe. The predicted amino acid sequence of the frp1+ gene exhibits hydrophobic regions compatible with transmembrane domains. It shows similarity to the Saccharomyces cerevisiae FRE1 gene product and the gp91-phox protein, a component of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase that is deficient in X-linked chronic granulomatous disease.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## References\n\n1.  1.  Plant Physiol. 1972 Aug;50(2):208-13 - [PubMed](/16658143/)\n2.  1.  Biochem J. 1992 Jun 15;284 ( Pt 3):781-8 - [PubMed](/1320378/)\n3.  1.  FEBS Lett. 1990 Jul 30;268(1):217-21 - [PubMed](/1974520/)\n4.  1.  Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 1988 Apr;85(8):2444-8 - [PubMed](/3162770/)\n5.  1.  Genomics. 1989 Nov;5(4):874-9 - [PubMed](/2687159/)\n\nShow all 27 references\n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   Alleles\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Alleles%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Alleles)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Amino Acid Sequence\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Amino+Acid+Sequence%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Amino+Acid+Sequence)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Animals\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Animals%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Animals)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Base Sequence\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Base+Sequence%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Base+Sequence)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Cattle\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Cattle%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Cattle)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Cloning, Molecular\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Cloning%2C+Molecular%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Cloning%2C+Molecular)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   DNA, Fungal / isolation & purification\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22DNA%2C+Fungal%2Fisolation+and+purification%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=DNA%2C+Fungal)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   FMN Reduct