: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO Issue 27593\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+This change creates a molecular function catalytic activity term for a RHEA-backed oxidoreductase reaction and updates an existing ferric-chelate reductase term.\n+\n+## Pattern Decision\n+\n+No `intersection_of` logical definition was added. Existing GO catalytic activity terms in this area are represented with:\n+\n+- `namespace: molecular_function`\n+- a reaction-based definition using `Catalysis of the reaction: ...`\n+- RHEA as the definition source and exact xref where available\n+- asserted `is_a` placement under the relevant oxidoreductase parent\n+\n+Relevant precedent:\n+\n+- `GO:0052851 ferric-chelate reductase (NADPH) activity` uses a RHEA reaction definition, `xref: RHEA:28795 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}`, and parentage to `GO:0000293` and `GO:0016723`.\n+- `GO:0140618 ferric-chelate reductase (NADH) activity` follows the same pattern with `RHEA:15061`.\n+\n+## Applied Pattern\n+\n+The new term `GO:7770068 ferric iron reductase activity` follows the catalytic activity/RHEA pattern and is placed under `GO:0016723 oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions, NAD or NADP as acceptor`.\n+\n+`GO:0000293 ferric-chelate reductase activity` is made a child of the new broader ferric iron reductase term and its definition is corrected from siderophore-specific wording to chelate wording on both substrate and product sides.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+# Research Notes for GO Issue 27593\n+\n+## RHEA:71767\n+\n+The bundled RHEA RDF used by the ontology build lists `RHEA:71767` as approved and chemically balanced:\n+\n+* SUPPORT: RHEA:71767 \"2 Fe(2+) + NADP(+) + H(+) = 2 Fe(3+) + NADPH\"\n+    - The RHEA record also lists the reverse directional reaction as `RHEA:71769`: `2 Fe(3+) + NADPH => 2 Fe(2+) + NADP(+) + H(+)`.\n+\n+## PMID:8321236 \"The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase\"\n+\n+This publication is the original characterization of fission yeast `frp1+` as required for ferric iron uptake and cell-surface ferric reductase activity.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:8321236 \"We have identified a cell surface ferric reductase activity in the fission yeast Schizosaccharomyces pombe.\"\n+    - The abstract states that a mutant deficient in this activity was also deficient in ferric iron uptake.\n+    - The abstract states that `frp1+` shows similarity to the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase component gp91-phox.\n+\n+## PMID:34614242 \"Fission yeast RNA-binding proteins Puf2 and Puf4 are involved in repression of ferrireductase Frp1 expression in response to iron\"\n+\n+This study supports Frp1 as a ferrireductase in the reductive iron uptake pathway and documents regulation of Frp1 expression.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:34614242 \"Cells expressing Puf2 and Puf4 stimulate decay of the frp1+ mRNA encoding a key enzyme of the reductive iron uptake pathway.\"\n+    - The abstract reports enhanced ferrireductase activity when `frp1+` mRNA is stabilized in `puf2őĒ puf4őĒ` mutant cells.\n+\n+## PMID:39940646 \"The Ferroxidase-Permease System for Transport of Iron Across Membranes: From Yeast to Humans\"\n+\n+This review provides current background on iron transport systems across membranes, including yeast iron uptake context.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:39940646 \"Transport of iron across the cell membrane is a tightly controlled process carried out by specific proteins in all living cells.\"\n+    - The abstract reviews yeast and human iron transport systems and their protein components.\n+\n+## Validation Notes\n+\n+`linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:8321236` completed successfully. Attempts to cache `PMID:34614242` and `PMID:39940646` hit NCBI HTTP 429 rate limiting, so PubMed pages were fetched directly for title, PMID, DOI, and abstract confirmation.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM terms/GO_0000293.obo\nA terms/GO_7770068.obo\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA RESEARCH.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo\n@@ -1,12 +1,13 @@\n [Term]\n id: GO:0000293\n name: ferric-chelate reductase activity\n namespace: molecular_function\n-def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe3+-siderophore + electron donor = 2 Fe2+-siderophore + electron acceptor.\" [PMID:33559753]\n+def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe3+-chelate + electron donor = 2 Fe2+-chelate + electron acceptor.\" [PMID:33559753]\n synonym: \"ferric chelate reductase activity\" EXACT []\n synonym: \"iron chelate reductase activity\" EXACT []\n+is_a: GO:7770068 ! ferric iron reductase activity\n is_a: GO:0016722 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions\n property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/21029\" xsd:anyURI\n property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26726\" xsd:anyURI\n property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30815\" xsd:anyURI\n-\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27593\" xsd:anyURI\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770068.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770068.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770068.obo\n@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:7770068\n+name: ferric iron reductase activity\n+namespace: molecular_function\n+def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe(2+) + NADP+ + H+ = 2 Fe(3+) + NADPH.\" [PMID:8321236, PMID:34614242, PMID:39940646, RHEA:71767]\n+synonym: \"ferric reductase activity\" EXACT []\n+synonym: \"NADPH:Fe(3+) oxidoreductase activity\" RELATED []\n+xref: RHEA:71767 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\n+is_a: GO:0016723 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions, NAD or NADP as acceptor\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27593\" xsd:anyURI\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+creation_date: 2026-05-10T02:12:33Z\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO Issue 27593\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+This change creates a molecular function catalytic activity term for a RHEA-backed oxidoreductase reaction and updates an existing ferric-chelate reductase term.\n+\n+## Pattern Decision\n+\n+No `intersection_of` logical definition was added. Existing GO catalytic activity terms in this area are represented with:\n+\n+- `namespace: molecular_function`\n+- a reaction-based definition using `Catalysis of the reaction: ...`\n+- RHEA as the definition source and exact xref where available\n+- asserted `is_a` placement under the relevant oxidoreductase parent\n+\n+Relevant precedent:\n+\n+- `GO:0052851 ferric-chelate reductase (NADPH) activity` uses a RHEA reaction definition, `xref: RHEA:28795 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}`, and parentage to `GO:0000293` and `GO:0016723`.\n+- `GO:0140618 ferric-chelate reductase (NADH) activity` follows the same pattern with `RHEA:15061`.\n+\n+## Applied Pattern\n+\n+The new term `GO:7770068 ferric iron reductase activity` follows the catalytic activity/RHEA pattern and is placed under `GO:0016723 oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions, NAD or NADP as acceptor`.\n+\n+`GO:0000293 ferric-chelate reductase activity` is made a child of the new broader ferric iron reductase term and its definition is corrected from siderophore-specific wording to chelate wording on both substrate and product sides.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+# Research Notes for GO Issue 27593\n+\n+## RHEA:71767\n+\n+The bundled RHEA RDF used by the ontology build lists `RHEA:71767` as approved and chemically balanced:\n+\n+* SUPPORT: RHEA:71767 \"2 Fe(2+) + NADP(+) + H(+) = 2 Fe(3+) + NADPH\"\n+    - The RHEA record also lists the reverse directional reaction as `RHEA:71769`: `2 Fe(3+) + NADPH => 2 Fe(2+) + NADP(+) + H(+)`.\n+\n+## PMID:8321236 \"The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase\"\n+\n+This publication is the original characterization of fission yeast `frp1+` as required for ferric iron uptake and cell-surface ferric reductase activity.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:8321236 \"We have identified a cell surface ferric reductase activity in the fission yeast Schizosaccharomyces pombe.\"\n+    - The abstract states that a mutant deficient in this activity was also deficient in ferric iron uptake.\n+    - The abstract states that `frp1+` shows similarity to the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase component gp91-phox.\n+\n+## PMID:34614242 \"Fission yeast RNA-binding proteins Puf2 and Puf4 are involved in repression of ferrireductase Frp1 expression in response to iron\"\n+\n+This study supports Frp1 as a ferrireductase in the reductive iron uptake pathway and documents regulation of Frp1 expression.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:34614242 \"Cells expressing Puf2 and Puf4 stimulate decay of the frp1+ mRNA encoding a key enzyme of the reductive iron uptake pathway.\"\n+    - The abstract reports enhanced ferrireductase activity when `frp1+` mRNA is stabilized in `puf2őĒ puf4őĒ` mutant cells.\n+\n+## PMID:39940646 \"The Ferroxidase-Permease System for Transport of Iron Across Membranes: From Yeast to Humans\"\n+\n+This review provides current background on iron transport systems across membranes, including yeast iron uptake context.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:39940646 \"Transport of iron across the cell membrane is a tightly controlled process carried out by specific proteins in all living cells.\"\n+    - The abstract reviews yeast and human iron transport systems and their protein components.\n+\n+## Validation Notes\n+\n+`linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:8321236` completed successfully. Attempts to cache `PMID:34614242` and `PMID:39940646` hit NCBI HTTP 429 rate limiting, so PubMed pages were fetched directly for title, PMID, DOI, and abstract confirmation.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo","relativePath":"terms/GO_0000293.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0000293.obo\n@@ -1,12 +1,13 @@\n [Term]\n id: GO:0000293\n name: ferric-chelate reductase activity\n namespace: molecular_function\n-def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe3+-siderophore + electron donor = 2 Fe2+-siderophore + electron acceptor.\" [PMID:33559753]\n+def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe3+-chelate + electron donor = 2 Fe2+-chelate + electron acceptor.\" [PMID:33559753]\n synonym: \"ferric chelate reductase activity\" EXACT []\n synonym: \"iron chelate reductase activity\" EXACT []\n+is_a: GO:7770068 ! ferric iron reductase activity\n is_a: GO:0016722 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on metal ions\n property_value: term_tracker